nts1.d:
In Iceland, Thomas Stankiewicz contemplates the constant flux of the elements. A composer & musician in his own right, he selectively weaves in between soundtracks, classical music, and evocative ambient sounds, symphonically unveiling untold stories from past and future…
@tommmasi
Minus Kendal trods the outer reaches foraging for aural morsels, slinging you a monthly smorgasbord of sultry sonix from trenchcoat folk to silicone synthwave.

Kit Grill presents a monthly excursion into music from around the world. Sunday, monthly, 4-5pm GMT.
kitgrill.com
The man behind the various Emotional labels jumps in the NTS cockpit for a chance to show off his expansive taste.
Janie Jones delivers an hour a month of kraut, psych and other treats.

London Perfect Lives shopkeepers Bruno and Danny share an hour of discoveries each month, Dipping into charming private press releases, cozy dub & dancehall, way out of left-field synth pop & postpunk, among other surprises..

nts1.n: NTS Guide to: New York Soul
nts1.d: A world-class music city, New York has never been the first thought when it comes to soul - to most people soul means Detroit, or Memphis, Chicago, or Philadelphia. However, there was a flourishing of soul artists in NYC simultaneous to these other more notable cities. This hour long selection guides us through some lesser heard soul records from New York, dating from the 1960s and '70s.

nts1.n: MIDNIGHT MARAUDERS W/ MARSHMELLO & ADRIAN YOUNGE
nts1.d: Marsha by name and mellow by nature, MarshmeLLo takes you on a musical journey of all her influences plus a little extra. The first show ever broadcast on the station, Marsha continues to find her groove…

nts1.n: VIBRATIONS FOR A BETTER WORLD W/ AOKI TAKAMASA (R)

nts1.d: Mosca runs underground club music inspired by tunes from all over: dub, house, techno, grime and jungle, as well as East coast hip hop, South African house, Shaolin soul, indie and post-rock from his youth, first-wave electro, stripped down ragga and dancehall, a little minimal ghetto stuff, and more. On top of that he's racked up some pretty big guest mixes in past shows.

nts2.d: Music Supervisor and DJ Dhamirah Coombes brings a monthly multi-genre curation of m00d-bending tracks intended for a deep listening experience.
Children of Zeus's Konny Kon takes over our Manchester studio once a month to play upfront Soul, Classic Hip Hop & New RnB.
All Hands On Deck co-founder Abena jumps on once a month - music to help loosen your joints, live from the Manchester studio. Expect dub, techno & a bit of ambient.

Known for their boundary pushing, often challenging electronic productions, and pioneering experiential live performances, the duo of Sheffield's Mark Fell and Mat Steel deviated from their city's tradition for more straightforward bleep and techno offshoots to create sparse, minimal and repetitive competitions that favour gentle insistence over high impact.
"we focus on leaving the audience feeling cold, not just a lack of interest in trying to engage anyone, but more like deliberately avoiding this… no dynamic changes in beats or nodding heads behind powerbooks, just large, awkward, immobile slabs of form. Imagine a Zen Buddhist with unresolved emotional issues. For me, thats how this particular "vibe" relates to minimal or formal aesthetics." - Mark Fell

nts2.n: RED LASER RECORDS w/ IL BOSCO
nts2.d: Red Laser Records crew brings Manchester's own blend of Manctalo, Disco & Boogie. A high energy Sunday Buzz guaranteed.
Memphis selector and radio host Nya presents an hour of rare soul, boogie, gospel, and funk records once a month.

nts2.d: Visual artist and founder and editor-in-chief of The Editorial Magazine Claire Milbrath joins us for an hour of ambient, classical, and italian library music.

nts2.n: All Night Flight w/ Kaity Fox
nts2.d: A winding journey through the catalogue of All Night Flight's Stockport record store, spanning from modern classical and free-flowing jazz to a wide soundscape of dark ambient, folk and techno… with All Night Flight, anything goes!

nts2.d: Two hours of Canadian-made cassette ambient, new age and downtempo sounds from the 1980s, selected by NTS.
Eclectic record selections and guest chats with Parisian crate digger, producer, & DJ Onra.
Los Angeles native & synth pioneer Benedek blends ambient, boogie, funk & more, once a month from our LA studio.
An auditory exploration with SF native Mishka ranging from synth pop and balearic to softrock and global dance gems. One hour, once a month, with love.

subtle.d: 2Step Selects is a monthly show hosted by the Choki Biki Records crew. Founded in Dublin, Ireland, CBR consists of DJ Sharpson, 2step.png, Frame Shift, and MICK. The show consists of an all round breaks, electro, ukg and jungle hour, followed by an Irish showcase, demonstrating all the best Ireland has to offer collective/party/Dj & Producer wise!

Saraphim (aka RNS & RDubz) are two Essex based Producer/DJ’s currently focused on Dubstep & the 140 spectrum, mixing ethnical and grime influences into their music. You can expect anything from deep and melodic meditative vibes to high energy driven music.
London based DJ who enjoys exploring the darker, bassier corners of Jungle, Breaks, Techno and Drum & Bass, especially when it is laced with a bit of acid.

subtle.n: The Ice Box Sessions with Frigid

subtle.d: Hailing from northern Italy, STANDARD is a collective of artists, DJs and producers that aims at the promotion of bass music: Garage, UK Funky, Breaks, Leftfield Bass, Leftfield Techno, Dubstep, everything in between and beyond. They focus on the Italian Bass scene, showcasing new up-and-coming artists as well as established talents from all over the peninsula.

Oddkut is a producer & DJ hailing from Balakovo City, Russia. He's part of the Russian collective "United Gang" who are a Moscow-based community of local musicians, DJ's and promoters teamed up by their genuine love & interest in UK underground music, "TAЭT VREMYA" art group and the creator of the Moscow parties "Judder".

dublab.d: “Dying Songs focuses on melancholic electronic music but isn’t limited to that. Sometimes it gets dark, sometimes I try to mix techno awkwardly, sometimes i get nostalgic… I like stuff that’s dreamy, ghostly, pretty and sad. I’ll try out new productions of my own, as well. I’m keeping it pretty open and we’ll see how it evolves.” – Jimmy

dublab.n: Daddy Differently and Dirty Dave - Things of Life
dublab.d: It’s the simple things isn’t it? The little things of life. Good food, sunshine, no traffic, dark coffee, 72˚ breeze, telephone off the hook and music every Friday morning a la Daddy Differently & Dirty Dave.
